<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="227" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,1578,2035]" pageId="2" pageNumber="227">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,304,1686,1711]" pageId="2" pageNumber="227">Remark.</emphasis>
The nominate taxon of 
<taxonomicName authority="(Toulgoet, 1954)" authorityName="Toulgoet" authorityYear="1954" baseAuthorityName="Toulgoet" baseAuthorityYear="1954" box="[580,962,1686,1711]" class="Insecta" family="Nolidae" genus="Nola" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="227" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="biangulata">
<emphasis box="[580,764,1686,1711]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="227">Nola biangulata</emphasis>
(Toulgoet, 1954)
</taxonomicName>
was described from 
<collectingCountry box="[1201,1339,1686,1711]" name="Madagascar" pageId="2" pageNumber="227">Madagascar</collectingCountry>
. Later, a closely related species was found in 
<collectingCountry box="[572,673,1722,1747]" name="Tanzania" pageId="2" pageNumber="227">Tanzania</collectingCountry>
which subsequently have been described as 
<taxonomicName authority="Fibiger &amp; Legrain, 2009" authorityName="Fibiger &amp; Legrain" authorityYear="2009" class="Insecta" family="Nolidae" genus="Nola" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="227" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="usambai">
<emphasis box="[1186,1314,1722,1747]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="227">N. usambai</emphasis>
Fibiger &amp; Legrain, 2009
</taxonomicName>
. In his revision Hacker downgraded the taxon as subspecies of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Toulgoet" baseAuthorityYear="1954" box="[1032,1187,1758,1783]" class="Insecta" family="Nolidae" genus="Nola" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="227" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="biangulata">
<emphasis box="[1032,1187,1758,1783]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="227">N. biangulata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and at the same time described an other closely related species 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hacker" authorityYear="2012" box="[627,844,1794,1819]" class="Insecta" family="Nolidae" genus="Nola" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="227" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="submelanoscelis">
<emphasis box="[627,844,1794,1819]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="227">N. submelanoscelis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry box="[915,1060,1794,1819]" name="South Africa" pageId="2" pageNumber="227">South Africa</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Hacker, H. H. &amp; Schreier, H. P. &amp; Goater, B." box="[1075,1285,1794,1819]" pageId="2" pageNumber="227" pagination="7 - 612" refId="ref13560" refString="Hacker, H. H., Schreier, H. P. &amp; Goater, B. (2012) Revision of the tribe Nolini of Africa and the Western Palaearctic Region (Lepidoptera, Noctuoidea, Noctuidae, Nolinae). Esperiana, 17, 7 - 612." type="journal article" year="2012">
Hacker 
<emphasis box="[1166,1216,1794,1819]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="227">et al</emphasis>
2012
</bibRefCitation>
). As all three taxa have nearly identical genitalia, distinguishing 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hacker" authorityYear="2012" box="[716,932,1830,1855]" class="Insecta" family="Nolidae" genus="Nola" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="227" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="submelanoscelis">
<emphasis box="[716,932,1830,1855]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="227">N. submelanoscelis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
on species rank is not justified, therefore it is downgraded here to subspecies rank. The distribution area of the southern African subspecies of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Toulgoet" baseAuthorityYear="1954" box="[1285,1406,1866,1891]" class="Insecta" family="Nolidae" genus="Nola" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="227" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="biangulata">
<emphasis box="[1285,1406,1866,1891]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="227">biangulata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is probably restricted to the lowland coastal bushveld-grassland of Southern Africa. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hacker" authorityYear="2012" box="[1087,1436,1902,1927]" class="Insecta" family="Nolidae" genus="Nola" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="227" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="biangulata" subSpecies="submelanoscelis">
<emphasis box="[1087,1436,1902,1927]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="227">N. biangulata submelanoscelis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from the Tanzanian subspecies by its considerably darker, more brownish forewing ground colour and its considerably smaller size, as these features are also well expressed on the specimen collected in the 
<collectingRegion box="[1260,1347,1975,1998]" country="Mozambique" name="Maputo" pageId="2" pageNumber="227">Maputo</collectingRegion>
Special Reserve. New country record for 
<collectingCountry box="[525,677,2010,2035]" name="Mozambique" pageId="2" pageNumber="227">Mozambique</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
